<body>
<div id="gnav-host" data-root="../"></div>

<section class="mig-hero">
  <h1>Adopt prism on an existing app — safely.</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    A two-line install ships visible improvements without touching
    your <code>.cms</code> source. This page summarises what changes,
    what to watch for, and how to roll back if anything looks off.
  </p>
</section>

<main class="mig-shell">

  <section class="mig-section">
    <h2>Pre-flight checklist</h2>
    <p class="lead-2">Five things to verify <em>before</em> you install. Skipping any of these is the most common cause of post-install surprises.</p>
    <ol class="mig-checklist">
      <li><strong>Confirm Bootstrap 4.</strong> prism is built for the BS4 markup the runtimes emit. BS5 / BS3 apps aren't supported yet.</li>
      <li><strong>Inventory your custom CSS.</strong> Anything that uses <code>!important</code> on a Bootstrap class will beat prism's tokens — that's intentional and means your app overrides win.</li>
      <li><strong>Inventory custom JS.</strong> Look for jQuery DataTables, custom datepickers, custom row-click handlers. Tag those targets <code>data-cms-no-enhance</code> before installing.</li>
      <li><strong>Branding image.</strong> If the navbar uses a coloured logo (not white-on-primary), test against <code>--cms-primary</code>. Override the token if needed.</li>
      <li><strong>Pick a theme baseline.</strong> Default keeps the BS4 feel; Tabler is closest to typical admin UX; Material is the biggest visual departure.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="mig-section">
    <h2>What changes — see it side by side</h2>
    <p class="lead-2">
      A typical inventory list page, before and after a two-line install.
      Same Bootstrap 4 markup; the only difference is the prism CSS being loaded.
    </p>
    <div class="mig-diff">
      <div class="mig-diff-pane">
        <div class="mig-diff-label" style="color:#94a3b8"><span class="dot"></span>Before</div>
        <div class="mig-diff-frame"><iframe src="../sandbox.html?demo=toolbar-table" loading="lazy" title="bare BS4 table"></iframe></div>
      </div>
      <div class="mig-diff-pane">
        <div class="mig-diff-label" style="color:var(--link)"><span class="dot"></span>After</div>
        <div class="mig-diff-frame"><iframe src="../sandbox.html?demo=toolbar-table&amp;ui=1" loading="lazy" title="cms-ui table"></iframe></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mig-section">
    <h2>What changes — the surface map</h2>
    <p class="lead-2">Every visible delta on a typical CaseMaster page.</p>
    <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;font-size:0.9rem;box-shadow:var(--shadow)">
      <thead style="background:var(--surface-2)">
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left;padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);font-size:0.72rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--muted);font-weight:600">Surface</th>
          <th style="text-align:left;padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);font-size:0.72rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--muted);font-weight:600">Before</th>
          <th style="text-align:left;padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);font-size:0.72rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--muted);font-weight:600">After prism</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Tables</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Sharp, harsh stripes, blue header.</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Soft surface, muted-grey uppercase header, hover tint, sortable.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Buttons</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">BS4 default radii (4 px) and saturated colours.</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">8 px radii, slightly muted hover, focus rings.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Inputs</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">BS4 default 4 px radius, blue focus ring.</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">8 px radius, primary-coloured focus ring tied to <code>--cms-primary</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Cards</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Plain white panel with hairline border.</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Same panel + soft shadow, rounded corners.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Navbar</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)"><code>bg-primary</code> = BS4 blue.</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)"><code>bg-primary</code> = your <code>--cms-primary</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Modals</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Sharp 4 px corners.</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">14 px corners, larger drop shadow, blurred backdrop.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Pagination</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">BS4 attached buttons.</td><td style="padding:0.6rem 0.85rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border)">Detached buttons with subtle borders.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="mig-section">
    <h2>Gradual adoption</h2>
    <p class="lead-2">All-or-nothing isn't required. Two strategies for risk-averse teams:</p>

    <h3>Theme only first</h3>
    <p>Skip the JS bundle on the first pass:</p>
<pre><code>/* app.css */
@import url('/static/lib/prism/prism.min.css');
/* leave app.js alone for now */</code></pre>
    <p>You get the visual lift without any behavioural changes. Roll out the JS bundle in a second deploy once you've shaken out the visual side.</p>

    <h3>Per-page opt-out</h3>
    <p>Disable prism on a single fragile page even though it's installed globally:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;body data-cms-no-enhance&gt;</code></pre>
    <p>The whole page renders bare BS4. Useful for legacy reports / wizards while you migrate the rest.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="mig-section">
    <h2>Roll back</h2>
    <p class="lead-2">Two commented lines is all it takes. No migrations to undo, no leftover state.</p>

    <div class="mig-rollback">
      <strong>Roll back</strong>
      <pre style="margin:0"><code>/* app.css */
/* @import url('/static/lib/prism/prism.min.css'); */</code></pre>
      <pre style="margin:.6rem 0 0"><code>// app.js
// document.body.appendChild(s);  // (was the prism injection)</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="mig-cta">
    <a href="/docs/migration">Read the long-form migration guide →</a>
  </div>
</main>

<script src="/assets/site.js"></script>
<script src="/assets/nav.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
